            ['image' => 'https://picsum.photos/seed/t12/800/400', 'title' => 'Securing Your APIs: OAuth 2.0 and JWT Explained', 'description' => 'Authentication and authorization are among the most security-sensitive parts of any application. Understanding the OAuth 2.0 flows, JWT structure, and common pitfalls is essential for every backend developer building APIs that serve external clients.', 'body' => 'OAuth 2.0 delegates authorization to an identity provider, keeping credentials off your servers. JWTs encode claims in a signed, self-contained token that can be verified without a database lookup. The Authorization Code flow with PKCE is the recommended choice for web and mobile clients. Avoid storing JWTs in localStorage; use httpOnly cookies to prevent XSS theft. Always validate the algorithm, expiry, and audience claims on the server.', 'views' => 523, 'categories' => [1]],
